
[1]orpiment

   OR'PIMENT, n. [L. auripigmentum; aurum, gold, and pigmentum.]

   Sulphuret of arsenic, found native and then an ore of arsenic, or
   artificially composed. The native orpiment appears in yellow, brilliant
   and seemingly talcky masses of various sizes. The red orpiment is
   called realgar. It is more or less lively and transparent, and often
   crystallized in bright needles. In this form it is called ruby of
   arsenic.
